The promising [[England_national_under-19_football_team|England U19]] defender signed for [[Manchester_City_F.C.|Manchester City]] from [[Southampton_F.C.|Southampton]] on a three-and-a-half-year deal in January 2006.  A tall, athletic and composed centre back, Mills linked up again with City reserve boss [[Steve_Wigley|Steve Wigley]], who worked with the youngster during his spell in charge of [[Southampton_F.C._Academy|Saints' Academy]].  Mills displayed his potential during a handful of [[Football_League_Championship|Football League Championship]] appearances for the south-coast club, whilst also enjoying loan spells at [[A.F.C._Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] and [[Coventry_City_F.C.|Coventry City]].  On 26 January 2007, he joined [[Colchester_United_F.C.|Colchester United]]<ref>{{cite news|date=26 January 2007|url= http://newsimg.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/c/colchester_united/6301965.stm|title=Mills secures move to Colchester|publisher= BBC Sport|accessdate=31 July 2008 }}</ref> on loan, returning in April.
